# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# people_directory scratch & derived artifacts — never inputs to the pipeline.
#
# Tracked machinery: parse_raw.py, parse_extra.py, gen_directory.py,
# sync_vault.py, sync_fellowships.py, qc_directory.py, regen_guard.py, plus the
# source/derived JSON products and WORKFLOW.md. Everything below is regenerated
# by those (or by the underscore-prefixed analysis oneshots) and stays out of
# git. See WORKFLOW.md (sources-of-truth) + repo-root CLAUDE.md §7.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Underscore-prefixed analysis oneshots and their binary/JSON/HTML outputs
# (_louvain.py, _cluster_report.py, _X.npy, _graph.pkl, _communities.json,
# _REDESIGN_PREVIEW.html, …). CLAUDE.md §7: scratch scripts are never tracked.
# No tracked script or data file starts with an underscore, so this can't
# shadow a real file.
_*

# Regen-guard fingerprint cache — local debounce state, mirrors
# 01_data/index/source_state.json.
.regen_state.json

# Point-in-time weekly-QC reports — regenerated each run. The durable trend
# signal lives in qc_metrics.csv (tracked), cf. 02_logs/ run history ignored.
QC_REPORT_*.md

# Dated cluster/analysis dumps emitted by the _*.py oneshots (they hardcode a
# baked-in date; kept locally, out of git).
directory_analysis_*.html
people_*_20[0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9].html
people_*_20[0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9].csv

# Derived products that embed third-party PII (researcher emails). Regenerated
# by the pipeline (gen_directory.py / parse_extra.py) from vault sources, so a
# cloner rebuilds them locally; kept out of git to avoid publishing PII. The
# contract-bound RAG manifests under 01_data/ stay tracked (CLAUDE.md §3).
extra_data.json
ai-safety-people-directory.html

__pycache__/
.DS_Store
